Summary: A lightweight sentinel object that stands in for the library’s main interface until the user calls the initialization routine; any attribute or item access triggers an exception indicating that initialization has not yet occurred.

Business intent: Enforce correct startup sequence, give developers immediate feedback if they try to use the library before calling init, and avoid silent failures.
